==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tinning
<hw>Tin"ning</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act,
art, or process of covering or coating anything with melted tin, or with
tin foil, as kitchen utensils, locks, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The covering or lining of tin thus put on.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tinnitus</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
